==Finnish==

===Etymology===

[[Calque]] of either Swedish ''[[Österrike]]'' or German ''[[Österreich]]'': ''[[itä]]'' "east" + ''[[valta]]'', usually "[[power]]" but also "[[country]]" in compounds. See also ''[[Yhdysvallat]]''.

===Proper noun===
'''Itävalta'''

#[[Austria]], a country in Central Europe.

